# UI/UX & design system

## Styling

- Use **Tailwind CSS** for all styling (no ad-hoc inline styles except unavoidable cases like dynamic values).
- **Aesthetic**: Modern, minimalist, Linear.app–inspired: high contrast, generous whitespace, crisp typography.
- **Components**: Prefer **@shadcn/ui** primitives from `components/ui` (`Button`, `Input`, `Card`, etc.). Do **not** ship raw `<button>` / `<input>` for UI chrome—wrap or extend shadcn components.

## Spacing (4px grid)

- Treat spacing as multiples of **4px** (`gap-1` = 4px). Prefer **`gap-6`** between major sections/blocks and **`gap-2`** for tight groups (label + control, icon + text).

## Color

- **Brand**: Primary accent is **teal** (`--primary`, ~`#75D1C1`); body text is **charcoal** (`--foreground`, ~`#333`). See `app/globals.css`.
- **CTAs / primary actions**: `bg-primary text-primary-foreground` (tokens map to `hsl(var(--primary))` in `app/globals.css`).
- **Surfaces**: Light areas — subtle **`bg-zinc-50`**; dark sections — **`bg-slate-950`** (or theme `background` / `card` when matching existing pages).

## Interaction polish

- On interactive elements (buttons, links styled as buttons, cards with hover, inputs): include **`transition-all`**, **`duration-200`**, and subtle **`shadow-sm`** (add **`hover:`** / **`focus-visible:`** variants where it improves feedback).

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Primary CTA
<Button className="shadow-sm transition-all duration-200">Book</Button>

// ❌ Avoid for app UI
<button className="rounded px-4 py-2">Book</button>
```
